<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/9809633-matthew"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1482968499i/9809633._UX100_CR0,26,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/9809633-matthew">Matthew</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I would add to what afton hourigan said that the title also refers to the lawyer, Alfieri who narrates the play. He speaks to both Eddie and Marco and<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I would add to what afton hourigan said that the title also refers to the lawyer, Alfieri who narrates the play. He speaks to both Eddie and Marco and might be said to be a bridge between the characters. We see the play from his view.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
